19:
Yes, I already told you that! Besides,
isn't it obvious just by looking?!
23:
Undead, spirits, and now a
mushroom! Everything in this world
is so different from the organic life I
know!
26:
And that just makes it all the more
interesting! Surely I will learn
something new here!
31:
Goodness, this lad sure runs hot and
cold, don't he?
40:
Aye, but maybe a wee bit too
passionate.
43:
Actually, I think I've got the perfect
patient for you, lad. Mind coming
with me?
52:
Ohoho, they're already here, right in
front of you... Or should I say below?
57:
Wait, are you talking about... the
Spirit Tree?!
60:
It may be a mystical entity, but I
suppose that doesn't change the
fact that it's an organic life-form.
62:
It can still get sick or injured... And
therefore, it still needs a doctor.
68:
Exactly. Trees can get sick just like
people. And if the Spirit Tree gets
sick, so does our world.
72:
That's right... The first time I was
here, the world was a mess because
of the Spirit Tree.
76:
I've always taken care of the Spirit
Tree by meself, but I figured, why not
let someone else take a crack at it?
79:
Well, doctor? How do you feel about
treating an entire world?
85:
Heh... Ahahaha! Now this is
interesting! I would love to!
86:
But is this really acceptable? I know
that arboriculture exists, but that's
about the extent of my knowledge!
89:
Aye, 'tis fine. I'll be right 'ere sharing
me knowledge with you.
94:
Oh, thank you so much! I will pay
very close attention.
103:
...Aye, 'tis perfect! With this, the Spirit
Tree should be back to its spirited
self soon.
107:
What the—
When did it get so dark outside?!
110:
You're right. It's nearly dawn. Hehe... I
was so focused on our treatment
that I lost track of time.
113:
I'm sorry, lad. I didn't mean to push
you so hard.
116:
Not at all! But I am a bit concerned.
Was this really okay?
119:
The Spirit Tree is vital to your world.
Is it truly safe to teach me how to
treat it?
122:
Ah, not that I'm not grateful for the
opportunity!
127:
What're you saying? I just wanted to
help your studies, that's all. Besides...
128:
You seem like you're carrying quite
the burden already.
136:
To treat any and all who are
injured... Anybody going to those
lengths must have been through a
lot.
140:
...There used to be another android
of the same model as me... I
suppose you could call him my twin
brother.
142:
But one day, he and I were caught
up in an accident. He...
145:
So you've been carrying that around
all this time... Or perhaps...
146: Did you take on his will?
151:
...In a sense. As he was dying, he
passed his own parts on to me.
153:
By the time I rebooted, he had
already ceased to function. Even his
memory bytes were gone...
156:
My brother entrusted me with these
parts, so I too wish to leave
something behind someday.
159:
That's how everyone is. We take
something from others, and pass
them on to someone else.
161:
That goes for you, me... and even
those little rascals over there.
165:
Nngh... Ah! I-I'm so sorry. I fell asleep.
Is there anything I can do to help?!
168:
No worries, we just finished up the
Spirit Tree's treatment.
176:
Hehe, I suppose something did. I
realize I've learned a lot...
178:
Not just today, but up until now as
well. And I'm sure I'll learn even more
in the days to come.
